- 'Detailed information' includes operator symbol, operator type, description, syntax example, use cases, related operators, and difficulty level; 
- 'Performance impact' refers to the effect of an operator on the performance of a programming language, and can be 'significant', 'moderate', or 'minimal'.

sql:
SELECT language_name, popularity_score
FROM languages
WHERE popularity_score = (SELECT MAX(popularity_score) FROM languages);
